phases.content:
Implement the 5-guard bootstrap in `packages/framework/scripts/reconcile-state.mjs` (read `.tiki/research/reconciler-contract.md` first — it documents the contract, the applyTransition creation semantics, and the quantified stale-plan flood this rule must not trigger).

1. New helper `findBootstrapCandidates(state, tikiPath, now)` (export for tests): readdir `<tikiPath>/plans` (tolerate missing dir), match files via `/^issue-(\d+)\.json$/` (skips the archive/ subdir entry naturally). For each number N apply the guards IN ORDER and return candidate records `{ workId, number, plan, target }`:
   - skip if `state.activeWork["issue:" + N]` exists;
   - skip if N is in `history.recentIssues` (reuse `inHistory`);
   - skip if `<tikiPath>/plans/archive/issue-N.json` exists (archive presence = shipped, even where history predates the record);
   - skip if NOT recent: newest of plan.createdAt / plan.updatedAt / plan.auditedAt (parse defensively; unparseable/missing timestamps count as ABSENT, and a plan with NO parseable timestamp is NOT recent) must be within `BOOTSTRAP_RECENCY_MS = 14 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000` of `now`. Use plan JSON timestamps, NEVER file mtime (git clone/checkout resets mtime — would flood on fresh clones).
   - derive target: `deriveTarget(plan)`; if null but the plan parses and has `plan.issue.number === N`, fall back to `{ status: "planning", step: "PLAN" }` (a phases-empty plan is still a PLAN artifact). If the plan does not parse (`readPlanSafe` null) or `plan.issue.number !== N`, skip (filename/content mismatch = corrupt, do not bootstrap).
2. Wire into `reconcile()`'s pass: after the existing entry loop, iterate candidates and create each via `applyTransition(state, { workId, toStatus: target.status, toStep: target.step, phase: target.phase ?? null, parallelExecution: null, parentRelease: undefined, issue: { number: N, title: plan.issue.title ?? `Issue ${N}` }, release: null })` — applyTransition creates fresh entries when given an issue payload and performs NO legality check on creation, so no pre-guard needed. Push `{ workId, action: "bootstrapped at <STEP>" }` into result.changes (required for the write-only-on-change persistence).
3. Amend the SAFETY CONTRACT header: rule 1 gets a numbered amendment documenting the 5-guard bootstrap (#270) and why each guard exists (cite the ~120 stale-plan count).
4. Tests in `packages/framework/__tests__/reconcile-state.test.mjs` (ESM-import style, fixture .tiki trees, follow existing conventions; a `makePlan(overrides)` fixture helper with fresh timestamps will keep these terse):
   - positive: recent audited plan, empty activeWork → entry created at planning/AUDIT; recent plan with phase 2 executing of 3 → executing/EXECUTE phase {2,3,executing}; recent phases-empty plan → planning/PLAN;
   - TRAP per guard: archived copy exists → no creation; in history → no creation; stale timestamps (30 days old) → no creation; corrupt plan JSON → no creation; filename/issue-number mismatch → no creation;
   - existing-entry no-op: entry already present → bootstrap does not touch it (count unchanged);
   - RE-PIN the existing TRAP test 'a stale all-complete plan for an issue NOT in activeWork is never resurrected' so its fixture explicitly exercises the new rule (give its plan OLD timestamps and/or an archived copy so it stays a non-candidate under the new semantics — do not delete it, re-pin it).
5. Run the framework suite; all 74 existing + new tests green. Do NOT regenerate the dogfood copy yet (phase 2 does install.js regen + live-fire).
